  "prompt": "Is Khan Academy a good source to learn physics and mathematics?",
  "response": "Khan Academy is widely regarded as an excellent resource for learning physics and mathematics. Here are some pros and cons:\n\nPros:\n1. Free educational content\n2. Video lessons with clear explanations\n3. Step-by-step problem-solving tutorials\n4. Interactive exercises and practice problems\n5. Covers wide range of topics from basic to advanced levels\n6. Self-paced learning\n7. Structured curriculum\n\nCons:\n1. May lack depth for very advanced topics\n2. Less interactive compared to live classroom settings\n3. Not a substitute for formal education\n4. Limited personalized feedback\n5. Supplementary resource, not a complete standalone course\n\nOverall, Khan Academy is highly recommended as a supplementary learning tool for physics and mathematics, especially for students looking to:\n- Review concepts\n- Practice problem-solving\n- Prepare for exams\n- Learn at their own pace\n\nFor comprehensive learning, it's best used in combination with textbooks, classroom instruction, and additional practice materials.",
